<$TOP/mkfiles/mkfile.proto

# See mkfiles/arm64/mkfile for the flag rationale (-fsigned-char, gnu89, ...).
CC=gcc -c --std=gnu89 -Wno-cpp -fsigned-char
LD=gcc
AS=gcc
O=o

# used in tests/: the RISC-V (rv64) lineage. ja/jc/jl are the *same*
# binaries as ia/ic/il (assemblers/ia/mkfile, compilers/ic/mkfile,
# linkers/il/mkfile install them under both names); their main()s
# auto-select thechar='j' (64-bit) from argv[0]'s basename (or, for
# ia/il, a -j flag too), the original inferno 'i'/'j' dual-width riscv
# convention -- there is no separate top-level arch letter for riscv64
# the way arm64 got its own '7' distinct from arm's '5'. Object ext .j.
O_=j
CC_=jc
LD_=jl
AS_=ja
AR_=iar
